This is how to fib4 of n:
   When n is less than 2, then:
      The answer is n
   End when
   When n is 2, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   When n is 3, then:
      The answer is 2
   End when
   Remember that a is 0
   Remember that b is 1
   Remember that c is 1
   Remember that d is 2
   Remember that i is 4
   Do this diff of n and 3 times:
      Remember that next is sum of a and (sum of b and (sum of c and d))
      Remember that a is b
      Remember that b is c
      Remember that c is d
      Remember that d is next
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is d
